          <h4>Ticketing and ITSM</h4>
          <h3>Turn vulnerability findings into tracked work</h3>
          <p>Automatically create tickets when Fleet detects new CVEs or policy failures, so remediation lives in the same tool your team already uses, with no manual triage.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="detail-vendors">
          <span class="vendor-tag">Jira</span>
          <span class="vendor-tag">ServiceNow</span>
          <span class="vendor-tag">Zendesk</span>
          <span class="vendor-tag">Any system via webhooks</span>
        </div>
        <div purpose="detail-grid">
          <div purpose="use-cases">
            <p purpose="detail-subheading">Top use cases</p>
            <div purpose="use-case"><span purpose="use-case-num">1</span><p><strong>Auto-create Jira tickets for CVEs.</strong> Fleet detects a new vulnerability and opens a Jira issue with affected hosts, severity, and remediation context.</p></div>
            <div purpose="use-case"><span purpose="use-case-num">2</span><p><strong>Policy failure routing.</strong> Send webhook notifications when hosts fail compliance policies, routing them to your service desk.</p></div>
            <div purpose="use-case"><span purpose="use-case-num">3</span><p><strong>SLA tracking for patches.</strong> Combine Fleet vulnerability data with ticket timestamps to measure and enforce patch SLAs.</p></div>
          </div>
          <div purpose="how-it-works">
            <p purpose="detail-subheading">How it works</p>
            <div purpose="how-step"><span purpose="how-dot"></span><p>Enable Fleet's built-in Jira integration or configure webhook URLs for any ticketing system.</p></div>
            <div purpose="how-step"><span purpose="how-dot"></span><p>Fleet sends structured payloads with host details, CVE IDs, severity, and policy context, ready for ticket templates.</p></div>
            <div purpose="how-step"><span purpose="how-dot"></span><p>Outbound webhooks fire on CVE detection, policy failure, or host status changes. No polling needed.</p></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <a purpose="back-to-overview" href="#stack-hub">Back to overview</a>
      </div>


      <%// ─── DETAIL: SOAR ────────────────────────────────────── %>
