        <div purpose="detail-heading">
          <h4>SOAR and workflow automation</h4>
          <h3>Automate response without writing code</h3>
          <p>Connect Fleet events to no-code platforms so when a host goes offline, a policy fails, or a new vulnerability appears, your runbooks execute automatically.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="detail-vendors">
          <span class="vendor-tag">Tines</span>
          <span class="vendor-tag">Torq</span>
          <span class="vendor-tag">Swimlane</span>
          <span class="vendor-tag">Custom webhooks</span>
        </div>
        <div purpose="detail-grid">
          <div purpose="use-cases">
            <p purpose="detail-subheading">Top use cases</p>
            <div purpose="use-case"><span purpose="use-case-num">1</span><p><strong>Automated incident playbooks.</strong> Fleet detects a compromised host. Tines isolates the device, alerts the SOC, and opens an incident ticket.</p></div>
            <div purpose="use-case"><span purpose="use-case-num">2</span><p><strong>Self-healing compliance.</strong> A SOAR playbook auto-remediates drift, re-enabling FileVault, pushing a missing profile, or notifying the user.</p></div>
            <div purpose="use-case"><span purpose="use-case-num">3</span><p><strong>Enrichment workflows.</strong> Use Fleet's API to enrich alerts in other tools with real-time device context: OS version, software, policy status.</p></div>
          </div>
          <div purpose="how-it-works">
            <p purpose="detail-subheading">How it works</p>
            <div purpose="how-step"><span purpose="how-dot"></span><p>Fleet sends webhook events (policy failure, CVE found, host offline) to your SOAR platform's trigger URL.</p></div>
            <div purpose="how-step"><span purpose="how-dot"></span><p>Your SOAR parses the payload and runs a workflow: Slack alerts, Jira tickets, API calls back to Fleet.</p></div>
            <div purpose="how-step"><span purpose="how-dot"></span><p>Fleet's REST API supports bidirectional communication, so your SOAR can query Fleet and trigger actions programmatically.</p></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <a purpose="back-to-overview" href="#stack-hub">Back to overview</a>
      </div>


